[Our thanks to Sabine for finding this report and Natalia for translating the Russian news report.

Immunity to anthrax, whether from a clinical exposure or from vaccination, is temporary, lasting at best 9 months. This is why it is wise to vaccinate livestock each spring before the summer anthrax season. That there was a measure of cover probably explains why just one animal was affected and not more. But it is early days yet.

The oblast of Kursk is on the western border of Russia with the Ukraine: see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kursk, but probably better seen in this map of the Ukraine: http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/commonwealth/ukraine.gif. - Mod.MHJ]

